TY  - JOUR
AU  - Newell, Richard G.
AU  - Jaffe, Adam B.
AU  - Stavins, Robert N.
T1  - The Induced Innovation Hypothesis and Energy-Saving Technological Change*
PY  - 1999
Y1  - 1999/08/01
DO  - 10.1162/003355399556188
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 114
IS  - 3
SP  - 941
EP  - 975
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - We develop a methodology for testing Hicks's induced innovation hypothesis by estimating a product-characteristics model of energy-using consumer durables, augmenting the hypothesis to allow for the influence of government regulations. For the products we explored, the evidence suggests that (i) the rate of overall innovation was independent of energy prices and regulations; (ii) the direction of innovation was responsive to energy price changes for some products but not for others; (iii) energy price changes induced changes in the subset of technically feasible models that were offered for sale; (iv) this responsiveness increased substantially during the period after energy-efficiency product labeling was required; and (v) nonetheless, a sizable portion of efficiency improvements were autonomous.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/003355399556188
ER  - 



